The current link provider API is designed that the provider is asked for all links when contents changes. For simple links this is easy but if the computation of link targets are expensive we should support a `resolve` model (like we allow to resolve code lenses and completion items). So the enhanced version would be

``` ts
interface DocumentLinkProvider {
  provideDocumentLinks():DocumentLinks[];
  resolveDocumenLink?: (link: DocumentLink) => DocumentLink
}
```

When compute all links (`provideDocumentLinks`) it will be enough to just give a range and only when a link is selected `resolveDocumentLink` is called to fill in the target (iff expensive to compute)

